This rifle has been SOLD ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

M1 Garand manufactured by Harrington & Richardson Arms (HRA) for US Government in 1955. There are no import parts or marks anywhere on this rifle. Performs and cycles flawlessly and is in very nice original condition.  The original USGI issue HRA barrel (Dec. 1955) is shiny, measures only 1 at muzzle and just 2 at throat. It has been sighted in for 100 yards and it exceeds accuracy of the US Army's specifications at time of issue.  The Bolt, Op rod, Trigger Group and Gas plug are all stamped HRA and have correct lot numbers for date of issue. All metal has original USGI finish. There is no rust or pitting anywhere. The walnut stock is also HRA. As you can see in the photos the stock is beautiful and does have strong US armory "eagle" cartouche as well as the "circle P" on handle. 

M1 Garands manufactured by Harrington and Richardson Arms are considered the finest quality of all four Garand manufacturers. To find one with this many original HRA parts is very rare. This Garand is not some piece of junk collection of mismatched parts you find at gun shows or elsewhere. It is a correct and complete functioning M1 Garand that would still pass inspection at Parris Island. It is both beautiful to hold and shoot. No modifications or alterations have been made and is competition worthy for John C. Garand matches. It is something that you will be proud to own and pass on down. - If you have any questions please don't hesitate to contact me. I am selling for economic reasons and will entertain reasonable offers - I have 3 Garands and one must be sacrificed.-Thanks.
